snippet: Egyptians celebrating today could be behind bars tomorrow.
abstract: Op-Ed article by Prof Khaled M Abou El Fadl contends Egyptian Army has reaffirmed despotic tradition in the Middle East by ousting Pres Mohamed Morsi; warns ouster of legitimately elected president does not bode well for future of Egypt and democracy in the region.

lead_paragraph: Egyptians celebrating today could be behind bars tomorrow.
